extends ../layouts/modern-layout

block layout-content
  br
  // Hero Section
  section.bg-gradient-primary.py-5
    .container
      .row.align-items-center
        .col-lg-10.mx-auto.text-center
          h1.display-4.fw-bold.mb-3
            i.bi.bi-people-fill.me-3
            | The Balanced Equation: Crafting the Perfect Project Team Mix
          h2.h3.mb-4 Achieving Project Success with a Balanced Team
          p.lead.mb-5.
            Learn how to create the perfect project team by combining the strengths
            of internal employees and external consultants for optimal success.

  // Main Article Content
  article#main-article
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-8.mx-auto

          // Article metadata and sharing
          .article-meta.text-muted.mb-4.text-center
            time(datetime=article ? article.publishedDate : '2024-01-29') #{article && article.publishedDate ? new Date(article.publishedDate).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' }) : 'January 29, 2024'}
            span.mx-2 •
            span by Mark Hazleton
            span.mx-2 •
            span #{article && article.estimatedReadTime ? article.estimatedReadTime : 5} min read

          // Table of Contents
          nav#table-of-contents.mb-5(aria-label='Table of Contents')
            .card.bg-light
              .card-header
                h3.card-title.mb-0.fw-bold
                  i.bi.bi-list-ul.me-2
                  | Table of Contents
              .card-body
                ul.list-group.list-group-flush
                  li.list-group-item: a.text-decoration-none(href='#team-member-types') What Makes a Great Team Member
                  li.list-group-item: a.text-decoration-none(href='#consultant-risks') When Consultants Take Over
                  li.list-group-item: a.text-decoration-none(href='#collaboration-power') The Power of Working Together
                  li.list-group-item: a.text-decoration-none(href='#internal-team') The Heart of the Company: Your Team
                  li.list-group-item: a.text-decoration-none(href='#external-consultants') Bringing in Fresh Ideas: Consultants
                  li.list-group-item: a.text-decoration-none(href='#creating-right-team') How to Create the Right Team
          // Article Content Section
          section#team-member-types.mb-5
            h2.h3.text-primary.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-star.me-2
              | What Makes a Great Team Member
            p.mb-4.
              Understanding the different types of team members helps build stronger,
              more effective project teams.

            .row.g-4.mb-4
              .col-md-6
                .card.h-100.border-warning
                  .card-header.bg-warning.text-dark
                    h4.card-title.mb-0
                      i.bi.bi-lightbulb.me-2
                      | Change Makers
                  .card-body
                    p.card-text.mb-3.
                      People or groups that help bring about change. They introduce new ideas
                      and ways to do things.
                    ul.list-unstyled
                      li.mb-2
                        i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-warning.me-2
                        | Spot what needs to get better or change
                      li.mb-2
                        i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-warning.me-2
                        | Suggest and put in place new ways or ideas
                      li.mb-2
                        i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-warning.me-2
                        | Question old methods and inspire new thinking
                      li.mb-2
                        i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-warning.me-2
                        | Help everyone adapt to new ways

              .col-md-6
                .card.h-100.border-success
                  .card-header.bg-success.text-white
                    h4.card-title.mb-0
                      i.bi.bi-shield-check.me-2
                      | Stability Keepers
                  .card-body
                    p.card-text.mb-3.
                      People who make sure things stay steady and reliable. They keep the core
                      of what the company is about the same.
                    ul.list-unstyled
                      li.mb-2
                        i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-success.me-2
                        | Stick to the company's main goals and values
                      li.mb-2
                        i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-success.me-2
                        | Make sure changes fit with long-term plans
                      li.mb-2
                        i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-success.me-2
                        | Keep things stable for everyone in the company
                      li.mb-2
                        i.bi.bi-check-circle.text-success.me-2
                        | Handle risks so the company can grow safely

          section#consultant-risks.mb-5
            h2.h3.text-danger.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-exclamation-triangle.me-2
              | When Consultants Take Over
            p.mb-4.
              While consultants bring valuable expertise, over-reliance can create risks
              that need careful management.

            .accordion#consultantRisks.mb-4
              .accordion-item
                h4.accordion-header#headingGoals
                  button.accordion-button(
                    type='button'
                    data-bs-toggle='collapse'
                    data-bs-target='#collapseGoals'
                    aria-expanded='true'
                    aria-controls='collapseGoals'
                  )
                    i.bi.bi-bullseye.me-2
                    | Goals Not Matching
                .accordion-collapse.collapse.show#collapseGoals(
                  aria-labelledby='headingGoals'
                  data-bs-parent='#consultantRisks'
                )
                  .accordion-body
                    p.
                      Consultants might focus more on making money than finding
                      cost-effective ways for the client.

              .accordion-item
                h4.accordion-header#headingDependence
                  button.accordion-button.collapsed(
                    type='button'
                    data-bs-toggle='collapse'
                    data-bs-target='#collapseDependence'
                    aria-expanded='false'
                    aria-controls='collapseDependence'
                  )
                    i.bi.bi-link.me-2
                    | Too Much Dependence
                .accordion-collapse.collapse#collapseDependence(
                  aria-labelledby='headingDependence'
                  data-bs-parent='#consultantRisks'
                )
                  .accordion-body
                    p.
                      Relying a lot on consultants can make a company too dependent
                      on outside help.

              .accordion-item
                h4.accordion-header#headingFit
                  button.accordion-button.collapsed(
                    type='button'
                    data-bs-toggle='collapse'
                    data-bs-target='#collapseFit'
                    aria-expanded='false'
                    aria-controls='collapseFit'
                  )
                    i.bi.bi-puzzle.me-2
                    | Not Fitting In
                .accordion-collapse.collapse#collapseFit(
                  aria-labelledby='headingFit'
                  data-bs-parent='#consultantRisks'
                )
                  .accordion-body
                    p.
                      Consultants might not mesh well with your company's way of doing things,
                      which can affect how well their solutions work in the long run.

              .accordion-item
                h4.accordion-header#headingCosts
                  button.accordion-button.collapsed(
                    type='button'
                    data-bs-toggle='collapse'
                    data-bs-target='#collapseCosts'
                    aria-expanded='false'
                    aria-controls='collapseCosts'
                  )
                    i.bi.bi-currency-dollar.me-2
                    | High Costs
                .accordion-collapse.collapse#collapseCosts(
                  aria-labelledby='headingCosts'
                  data-bs-parent='#consultantRisks'
                )
                  .accordion-body
                    p.
                      Having consultants run everything can get really expensive, especially
                      if things take longer than planned.

              .accordion-item
                h4.accordion-header#headingKnowledge
                  button.accordion-button.collapsed(
                    type='button'
                    data-bs-toggle='collapse'
                    data-bs-target='#collapseKnowledge'
                    aria-expanded='false'
                    aria-controls='collapseKnowledge'
                  )
                    i.bi.bi-brain.me-2
                    | Losing Know-How
                .accordion-collapse.collapse#collapseKnowledge(
                  aria-labelledby='headingKnowledge'
                  data-bs-parent='#consultantRisks'
                )
                  .accordion-body
                    p.
                      Consultants might leave and take their valuable insights and skills with them
                      if there's no good way to share what they know with the company.

            .alert.alert-warning.border-0.shadow-sm.mb-4
              .d-flex.align-items-start
                i.bi.bi-shield-check.text-warning.me-3.fs-4
                div
                  h5.alert-heading.mb-2 Prevention Strategy
                  p.mb-0.
                    To avoid these issues, make clear goals, manage things well, work together,
                    limit how much you rely on consultants, and regularly check that everything
                    is on track with the company's main goals.

          section#collaboration-power.mb-5
            h2.h3.text-info.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-people.me-2
              | The Power of Working Together
            p.mb-4.
              Working well together is key to a great project team. This happens when everyone's
              work adds up to more than what they could do alone. This mix is really strong when
              it combines people who like to shake things up with those who keep things steady.

            p.mb-4.
              Consultants bring in new ideas and ways to challenge the usual. But it's important
              that these new ideas fit with what the company is all about and its long-term plans.
              This mix makes sure new ideas work well and last.

          section#internal-team.mb-5
            h2.h3.text-primary.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-heart.me-2
              | The Heart of the Company: Your Team

            p.mb-4.
              Your team members are much more than just employees; they are the essence of your
              company's identity and the way things are accomplished. Their daily actions, decisions,
              and interactions shape the workplace culture, making it a living, breathing entity.

            .row.g-4.mb-4
              .col-lg-4
                .card.text-center.border-primary.h-100
                  .card-body
                    i.bi.bi-memory.display-6.text-primary.mb-3
                    h5.card-title Institutional Memory
                    p.card-text.small Beyond just keeping projects on track, your staff embodies the collective memory of your organization.
              .col-lg-4
                .card.text-center.border-success.h-100
                  .card-body
                    i.bi.bi-rocket.display-6.text-success.mb-3
                    h5.card-title Innovation Driver
                    p.card-text.small Their engagement and commitment are the driving forces behind innovation and efficiency.
              .col-lg-4
                .card.text-center.border-info.h-100
                  .card-body
                    i.bi.bi-shield.display-6.text-info.mb-3
                    h5.card-title Resilience & Adaptability
                    p.card-text.small Their adaptability and resilience are crucial, especially in times of change or uncertainty.

            p.mb-4.
              In nurturing this vital component of your company, fostering a positive, inclusive,
              and empowering work environment is essential. Recognizing achievements, encouraging
              professional growth, and ensuring that every voice is heard are key to maintaining
              the vibrancy and health of your company's heart.

          section#external-consultants.mb-5
            h2.h3.text-success.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-lightbulb.me-2
              | Bringing in Fresh Ideas: Consultants

            p.mb-4.
              Consultants are like a breath of fresh air for your projects, bringing with them
              a wealth of specialized knowledge and a fresh perspective that can be just what's
              needed to overcome challenges and seize new opportunities.

            .alert.alert-info.border-0.shadow-sm.mb-4
              .d-flex.align-items-start
                i.bi.bi-info-circle.text-info.me-3.fs-4
                div
                  h5.alert-heading.mb-2 Key Benefits
                  p.mb-0.
                    Their expertise, honed across diverse industries and situations, allows them
                    to introduce novel ideas and methods that might not have been considered within
                    the confines of your company's existing framework.

            p.mb-4.
              The role of consultants extends beyond just providing advice; they act as catalysts
              for change, challenging the status quo and encouraging your team to think outside the box.
              Their external viewpoint helps in identifying blind spots or inefficiencies in current processes.

            p.mb-4.
              However, to truly leverage the potential of consultants, it's crucial to ensure a good fit
              with your company's culture and to clearly define the scope and objectives of their engagement.

          section#creating-right-team.mb-5
            h2.h3.text-dark.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-gear.me-2
              | How to Create the Right Team

            p.mb-4.
              Creating the perfect team balance requires careful consideration of multiple factors
              and continuous evaluation.

            .card.border-primary.shadow-sm
              .card-header.bg-primary.text-white
                h5.card-title.mb-0
                  i.bi.bi-checklist.me-2
                  | Key Considerations
              .card-body
                .row.g-3
                  .col-md-6
                    .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-2
                      i.bi.bi-target.me-2.text-primary
                      strong What the project needs to achieve
                  .col-md-6
                    .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-2
                      i.bi.bi-puzzle-fill.me-2.text-warning
                      strong What skills are missing
                  .col-md-6
                    .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-2
                      i.bi.bi-people-fill.me-2.text-success
                      strong How well the team works together
                  .col-md-6
                    .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-2
                      i.bi.bi-share.me-2.text-info
                      strong Sharing what's learned
                  .col-md-6
                    .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-2
                      i.bi.bi-arrow-repeat.me-2.text-secondary
                      strong Being able to change and grow
                  .col-md-6
                    .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-2
                      i.bi.bi-graph-up.me-2.text-dark
                      strong How to check progress and adjust

            p.mt-4.mb-4.
              Choosing the right mix for your project team can lead to better results, more creative
              solutions, and make sure everything fits with the long-term goals of your company.

          // Back to Top link
          .text-center.mb-4
            a(href='#table-of-contents' class='btn btn-outline-primary')
              i.bi.bi-arrow-up-circle.me-2
              | Back to Top
